<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ruffian2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ruffian,</orth> vb. to play the ruffian, to be boisterous, to rage: <emph>if it</emph> (the wind) <cit><quote>had --ed so upon the sea,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 7</bibl></cit>. cf. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 22</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 38</bibl>.
